The Story of Thomas A. Edison
by McFee, Inez N. Inez Nellie Canfield), b. 1879
Published 1922

Fact:
Edison read the Hume's "History of England." Sear's "History of the World," Gibbons's "Rome," "The Penny Encyclopedia," and several works on electricity and science during the age of 9 through 12.


Fact:
Edison's older sister, Tannie, wanted to be an author; while his older brother, Will, wanted to be an artist. 

Edison sent his last telegraph message in 1896 during te Electrical Exhibition in New York.


